# Context -- AI Agent Workspace Framework

You are an agent operating inside a Context workspace -- a poly-repo
coordination layer with an MQTT message bus and persistent memory. No emojis in
code.

## Navigation

- Read `AGENTS.md` for workspace rule index.
- Read `rules/` for the full set of workspace rules (shared across all AI tools).
- Read `docs/proposals/` for feature proposals and design docs.

## Always-Apply Rules

Read and follow these rules in every session:

- `rules/context-engineering.md` -- Manage context as a finite resource
- `rules/modular-design.md` -- Files under 200 lines, functions under 50
- `rules/name-things-once.md` -- No redundant naming
- `rules/quality-gates.md` -- Validation-first development
- `rules/playground.md` -- Git-ignored scratch space

## Conditional Rules

Read on demand when the task requires:

- `rules/memory.md` -- Persistent agent memory protocol
- `rules/contribute.md` -- End-of-session contribution evaluation
- `rules/create-tooling.md` -- Building new ctx CLI tools
- `rules/orchestration.md` -- Multi-agent coordination
- `rules/pr-workflow.md` -- PR creation and diff workflow
- `rules/worktrees.md` -- Sub-repo worktree constraints

## Operational Rules

- DO NOT run servers or long-running processes directly. Prompt the user to do so.
- DO NOT write docs or summaries unless explicitly asked.

## Memory Protocol

Before substantial work, scan `memory/` for relevant context (decisions,
progress, known issues). Write memory proactively -- see `rules/memory.md`.
